I said I don't want to do this.

276
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:47,720
-Why not?
-Just because.

277
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,850
I'm not doing it.

278
00:22:49,930 --> 00:22:51,520
Why?

279
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,900
Why do you not want to do this?

280
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:55,770
You've been doing well
with the counseling.

281
00:22:55,860 --> 00:22:57,610
You need to face this to get better.

282
00:22:57,690 --> 00:23:00,820
Will you keep living as a doctor
who can't operate?

283
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,660
Maybe later.

284
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,490
I'll do it some other time.

285
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:07,830
When would it be?

286
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,750
It's about time
to stop torturing yourself.

287
00:23:20,340 --> 00:23:21,960
-Here.
-Thanks.

288
00:23:23,970 --> 00:23:25,590
Now you look like Cha Yu-ri.

289
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,720
Yu-ri.

290
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:31,180
Yes?

291
00:23:31,270 --> 00:23:32,980
For the past five years,

292
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:38,060
were you around me as well?

293
00:23:38,650 --> 00:23:42,610
Sure. I stuck around you all the time.

294
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:48,030
Even I forgot my birthday,
but you remembered it every year.

295
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:52,540
Maybe I was struggling not to forget you.

296
00:23:54,330 --> 00:23:55,920
I guess that's why.

297
00:23:57,630 --> 00:23:58,750
After you left,

298
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:01,550
it didn't really hit me at first.

299
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:04,010
When I studied abroad,

300
00:24:04,090 --> 00:24:06,510
we didn't see each other for about a year.

301
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:08,640
It was like that.

302
00:24:10,180 --> 00:24:12,390
I felt like you were just away
for a little bit.

303
00:24:14,770 --> 00:24:19,770
And once I realized that I would
never be able to see you again,

304
00:24:21,110 --> 00:24:23,030
I couldn't even eat.

305
00:24:23,940 --> 00:24:25,360
I just cried my eyes out.

306
00:24:26,740 --> 00:24:29,370
But after a little while,

307
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:32,120
I felt hungry again.

308
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,710
So I started to eat,

309
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:37,670
take care of Ha-jun,

310
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:38,880
and work.

311
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:44,130
And one day,

312
00:24:47,430 --> 00:24:48,510
I realized that

313
00:24:49,140 --> 00:24:51,100
I was forgetting about you.

314
00:24:53,810 --> 00:24:55,390
I just celebrated your birthdays

315
00:24:56,390 --> 00:24:58,270
because I wanted to cling on to you.

316
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:01,020
Because I was sorry for you.

317
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:05,570
And you knew it, right?

318
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,610
Of course, I did.

319
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:10,990
Actually I was sad
that you were forgetting about me.

320
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,240
But

321
00:25:16,450 --> 00:25:19,790
I was afraid if I wouldn't be forgotten.

322
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:25,960
Watching people
have hard times because of me,

323
00:25:27,010 --> 00:25:28,800
was real hell.

324
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:31,340
Gang-hwa?

325
00:25:35,890 --> 00:25:37,480
So you knew it too.

326
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:40,020
That Gang-hwa has a problem.

327
00:25:41,020 --> 00:25:43,440
I do. I was around him all the time.

328
00:25:44,980 --> 00:25:47,030
He recently received a probation.

329
00:25:47,110 --> 00:25:48,780
I found out about it later on though.

330
00:25:52,530 --> 00:25:54,410
That's what I did to him.

331
00:25:55,660 --> 00:25:56,910
I broke his heart.

332
00:25:56,990 --> 00:25:58,790
It's not your fault.

333
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,210
Isn't it like you died
because you wanted to.

334
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:04,590
But it was my choice.

335
00:26:07,130 --> 00:26:09,550
I just made him feel guilty.

336
00:26:29,030 --> 00:26:32,110
Where did she go leaving me alone?

337
00:26:35,030 --> 00:26:36,030
Oh, right.

338
00:26:37,790 --> 00:26:38,620
That's right.

339
00:26:43,580 --> 00:26:46,960
SUPERNATURAL POWERS
SHAMAN MS. MI-DONG

340
00:26:47,550 --> 00:26:50,340
SEO BONG-YEON

341
00:27:03,060 --> 00:27:06,020
I know you're a stone-hearted human,

342
00:27:06,610 --> 00:27:10,940
but how could you send them up
just like that?

343
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:12,490
My point.

344
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:14,990
I didn't even get to say goodbye. Damn it.

345
00:27:20,750 --> 00:27:22,290
You guys are not human.

346
00:27:24,210 --> 00:27:25,580
To Guk-bong...

347
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:27,880
I mean, to people,

348
00:27:28,130 --> 00:27:30,500
you guys are just demons
who should be sent up.

349
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,300
How could you say something so harsh?

350
00:27:32,380 --> 00:27:33,590
I know.

351
00:27:33,670 --> 00:27:36,590
So if you don't want to get caught
and sent up all of a sudden like them,

352
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:38,550
stop avoiding Guk-bong

353
00:27:38,930 --> 00:27:43,060
and get over your regrets in this world.

354
00:27:46,650 --> 00:27:48,060
This is really frustrating.

355
00:27:55,740 --> 00:27:56,860
Hello?

356
00:27:56,950 --> 00:27:58,240
Hello, ma'am.

357
00:27:58,910 --> 00:28:00,490
Do you make domiciliary visits?

358
00:28:00,830 --> 00:28:01,830
What?

359
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:10,420
Min-jeong. Believe it or not,

360
00:28:11,300 --> 00:28:12,300
it's true.

361
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:31,150
What are you doing?

362
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:33,280
Get off, Yu-ri.

363
00:28:34,860 --> 00:28:37,530
You said we'd hang out at my place.

364
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:39,620
We will drink. So I can't drive.

365
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:40,700
Let's walk.

366
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:47,000
I'm hungry. Let's go.

367
00:29:01,010 --> 00:29:02,300
-I'm so hungry.
-Me too.

368
00:29:02,390 --> 00:29:04,390
-I shouted too much.
-I know.

369
00:29:04,470 --> 00:29:07,440
I couldn't help it
because you drove so fast.

370
00:29:18,280 --> 00:29:19,280
-Is it here?
-Yes.

371
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:20,360
It's for us.

372
00:29:20,530 --> 00:29:22,320
-It just came right on time.
-I know.

373
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,410
-Please enjoy.
-Thank you.

374
00:29:24,490 --> 00:29:26,000
It's pork belly meat.

375
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:28,500
-Let's go.
-Mom, Yu-ri and Hyeon-jeong are here.

376
00:29:28,580 --> 00:29:30,750
Gosh, I can't wait.

377
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:34,340
-Let's eat.
-It must be really good.

378
00:29:35,590 --> 00:29:37,130
Hello, Ms. Jeon.

379
00:29:46,020 --> 00:29:49,980
CHA MU-PUNG, JEON EUN-SUK,
CHA YU-RI, CHA YEON-JI

380
00:30:28,180 --> 00:30:29,850
-It looks delicious.
-It's warm.

381
00:30:29,930 --> 00:30:30,940
My goodness.

382
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:33,100
-I'm hungry.
-It looks great.

383
00:30:33,190 --> 00:30:36,070
Here's a cold beer for you.

384
00:30:36,150 --> 00:30:37,900
Yeon-ji, you're the best.

385
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:39,440
We have five drinkers here.

386
00:30:39,530 --> 00:30:41,360
This is far from enough.

387
00:30:41,530 --> 00:30:43,240
I don't drink beer.

388
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:44,280
I like soju.

389
00:30:44,490 --> 00:30:47,740
I knew it. You're so my type.

390
00:30:48,700 --> 00:30:50,500
Mom, I'll get you soju.

391
00:30:50,580 --> 00:30:51,870
Here, Dad.

392
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:53,290
-My daughter is the best.
-Gosh.

393
00:30:53,370 --> 00:30:54,420
It's good, isn't it?

394
00:30:55,670 --> 00:30:58,050
-This is nice.
-Dad, please open this for me.

395
00:30:58,130 --> 00:30:59,510
Give me that.

396
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:01,050
All right.

397
00:31:03,010 --> 00:31:04,220
It's open.

398
00:31:04,890 --> 00:31:07,100
It flew away like this.

399
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,100
Let's drink.

400
00:31:09,180 --> 00:31:11,180
Here. Have some of this.

401
00:31:11,270 --> 00:31:12,980
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

402
00:31:13,060 --> 00:31:14,940
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

403
00:31:18,820 --> 00:31:20,440
It tastes so good.

404
00:31:23,450 --> 00:31:26,620
So we're all together with Hyeon-jeong.

405
00:31:26,700 --> 00:31:28,490
It's been so long since we did this.

406
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:29,740
I know.

407
00:31:29,830 --> 00:31:32,660
I've been too busy
working and raising my kid.

408
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:35,540
She was just afraid
she would remind us of Yu-ri,

409
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:37,590
so she was being thoughtful.

410
00:31:38,460 --> 00:31:40,050
Do you think I don't know that?

411
00:31:42,170 --> 00:31:43,760
I had no idea

412
00:31:44,340 --> 00:31:47,470
this day would come again.

413
00:31:47,550 --> 00:31:49,810
What are you doing, Dad? This isn't right.

414
00:31:49,890 --> 00:31:53,180
She's right. Why are you being so silly?

415
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:54,560
Okay. I get it.

416
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:56,480
-I'm done. It's over.
-It's over.

417
00:31:56,810 --> 00:31:59,650
-Mr. Cha, please stop.
-What's over?

418
00:31:59,730 --> 00:32:02,570
It's nothing.
Your dad is just being silly again.

419
00:32:02,650 --> 00:32:04,610
Do you say things like that?

420
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:05,780
Sure.

421
00:32:05,860 --> 00:32:06,990
She says all kinds of stuff.

422
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:09,120
-Gosh, Dad.
-Stop it.

423
00:32:11,290 --> 00:32:12,830
-It tastes good.
-So

424
00:32:13,370 --> 00:32:14,790
did you guys have fun?

425
00:32:14,870 --> 00:32:16,120
Yes. We had a lot of fun.

426
00:32:16,210 --> 00:32:19,500
Hyeon-jeong's driving has improved a lot.
She was too afraid to run at 50km before.

427
00:32:19,590 --> 00:32:20,880
Hey, that was a long time ago.

428
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:24,880
That's not true.
I was a novice driver back then.

429
00:32:24,970 --> 00:32:27,300
Still, 50km is too slow.

430
00:32:27,380 --> 00:32:30,180
Here, Yu-ri. Try this.

431
00:32:30,260 --> 00:32:32,510
You seem to have only one daughter.

432
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,850
You're my son. All right.

433
00:32:34,930 --> 00:32:37,690
I didn't know I was a son.

434
00:32:37,770 --> 00:32:41,480
All right. I should give this to my son.

435
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:43,820
Here. Good.

436
00:32:44,110 --> 00:32:45,650
Why don't we take a picture together?

437
00:32:45,740 --> 00:32:47,360
-Good.
-Let's do that.

438
00:32:47,450 --> 00:32:48,860
Do I look okay?

439
00:32:48,950 --> 00:32:50,700
-You look perfect.
-You look beautiful.

440
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:52,530
-Don't worry.
-You're always pretty.

441
00:32:52,620 --> 00:32:53,540
I'll put this on here.

442
00:32:53,620 --> 00:32:55,830
Gather together and look at the camera.

443
00:32:55,910 --> 00:32:57,210
Mr. Cha, come closer.

444
00:32:57,290 --> 00:32:58,830
One...

445
00:32:59,170 --> 00:33:00,500
Come closer to each other.

446
00:33:00,580 --> 00:33:03,170
-One...
-Is it how it works?

447
00:33:05,260 --> 00:33:06,550
Let me see the picture.

448
00:33:06,630 --> 00:33:08,630
I'll show you.

449
00:35:08,170 --> 00:35:11,260
I'm very grateful to Hyeon-jeong.

450
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,930
I'm always grateful to her.

451
00:35:15,430 --> 00:35:16,890
Did you like it, Yu-ri?

452
00:35:17,510 --> 00:35:19,220
Yes. I loved it.

453
00:35:20,890 --> 00:35:22,770
What was so good?

454
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:26,730
I liked the wind,

455
00:35:26,810 --> 00:35:28,270
I liked the air,

456
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:30,280
and I liked Hyeon-jeong next to me.

457
00:35:31,650 --> 00:35:33,030
I'm glad to hear that.

458
00:35:34,700 --> 00:35:36,910
Things will be always like that
from now on.

459
00:35:37,950 --> 00:35:40,990
We will have happy moments
like that every day, Yu-ri.

460
00:35:45,750 --> 00:35:46,880
Do you not want it?

461
00:35:47,670 --> 00:35:49,250
Of course, I want it.

462
00:35:52,630 --> 00:35:53,720
What?

463
00:35:55,590 --> 00:35:56,800
Dad.

464
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:58,470
Is Dad sleeping already?

465
00:35:59,470 --> 00:36:03,100
Dad, you can't sleep here.

466
00:36:03,930 --> 00:36:06,440
-My gosh.
-It's been less than a minute.

467
00:36:07,020 --> 00:36:09,690
It was somewhere around here. Where is it?

468
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:12,530
There it is. It says Misaeng.

469
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:17,740
What is he doing here?

470
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:22,120
Hey.

471
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,370
Gosh, it hurts.

472
00:36:26,460 --> 00:36:28,000
-It hurts.
-What are you doing here?

473
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:29,630
Gosh, it's not like that.

474
00:36:29,710 --> 00:36:30,840
Let go of me.

475
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,630
-It really hurts.
-Come here.

476
00:36:35,050 --> 00:36:37,930
Come here. I got you.

477
00:36:38,430 --> 00:36:40,640
-Just follow me.
-It hurts.

478
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:41,970
Hello.

479
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:45,140
Stay still. Stop.

480
00:36:45,230 --> 00:36:47,640
What's with your arms?

481
00:36:48,850 --> 00:36:49,980
Is something there?

482
00:36:50,060 --> 00:36:52,360
What have you been up to these days?

483
00:36:52,650 --> 00:36:54,320
Why is there a ghost around you?

484
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:56,030
What? A ghost?

485
00:36:56,110 --> 00:36:57,530
-Stay still.
-Ghost?

486
00:36:57,610 --> 00:36:59,450
I told you to stand still!

487
00:36:59,530 --> 00:37:00,660
Isn't it staying still?

488
00:37:01,240 --> 00:37:03,450
-It hurts.
-Stop it. Stay still.

489
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:12,750
Is he always so stupid like that?

490
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:16,010
Because she's not here.

491
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:17,670
Who?

492
00:37:18,010 --> 00:37:18,970
His wife.

493
00:37:19,260 --> 00:37:20,300
He's Hyeon-jeong's boy.

494
00:37:20,390 --> 00:37:22,390
Hyeon-jeong. Where are you?

495
00:37:24,140 --> 00:37:26,810
Hurry and come right away, Hyeon-jeong.

496
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:31,310
Gosh, you now know Yu-ri was around you
for five years.

497
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:32,940
Just come over here.

498
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:36,570
I didn't know about it.

499
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:38,570
Are you sure

500
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:40,570
there's a ghost next to you?

501
00:37:41,450 --> 00:37:44,030
Why? Why is it doing this to me?

502
00:37:44,410 --> 00:37:46,540
Is it because I refused
to write a fake diagnosis?

503
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:49,210
Gosh, it's no big deal.

504
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:54,380
"Gosh, it's no big deal."

505
00:37:56,340 --> 00:37:57,170
Then why?

506
00:37:58,090 --> 00:37:59,550
Why are you hanging around with him?

507
00:38:00,180 --> 00:38:01,550
Right. That one.

508
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:02,760
There's something

509
00:38:04,220 --> 00:38:05,850
only he can do for me.

510
00:38:08,430 --> 00:38:09,640
What?

511
00:38:11,770 --> 00:38:13,400
What is it?

512
00:38:13,770 --> 00:38:16,270
Ms. Mi-dong, please tell me what he says.

513
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:17,780
Why? Why is he doing this to me?

514
00:38:17,860 --> 00:38:21,360
So there's something
only you can do for him.

515
00:38:22,820 --> 00:38:23,950
What is it?

516
00:38:28,250 --> 00:38:29,870
Please tell my mom

517
00:38:30,620 --> 00:38:31,670
that I didn't

518
00:38:33,670 --> 00:38:34,790
kill myself.

519
00:38:39,460 --> 00:38:42,550
He knows that it wasn't a suicide.

520
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:45,970
What does he say?

521
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:48,520
What is it? What?

522
00:38:49,390 --> 00:38:51,600
Ms. Mi-dong, please.
I need a simultaneous interpretation.

523
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:53,600
I can't wait.

524
00:38:54,100 --> 00:38:56,270
I'm very anxious.

525
00:39:26,260 --> 00:39:27,850
It must've been fun

526
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:36,520
to see how much I loved her
like some kind of an idiot.

527
00:39:43,950 --> 00:39:45,820
No, it wasn't like that.

528
00:39:48,490 --> 00:39:50,240
Do you know what I said?

529
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:55,580
I said I'm curious about her
because she looks like Seo-woo's mom.

530
00:39:57,580 --> 00:39:58,840
That I'm envious

531
00:40:00,050 --> 00:40:01,670
because she looks like Seo-woo.

532
00:40:04,130 --> 00:40:05,340
I had no idea.

533
00:40:07,470 --> 00:40:08,850
I was like a fool.

534
00:40:21,900 --> 00:40:24,070
You should've told me first.

535
00:40:29,950 --> 00:40:31,790
That's what you should've done.

536
00:40:42,090 --> 00:40:44,300
It has been a while

537
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:48,550
since you looked so happy

538
00:40:50,970 --> 00:40:53,520
when you were around other people.

539
00:40:56,810 --> 00:40:58,020
I was afraid

540
00:41:00,270 --> 00:41:01,650
you would get hurt.

541
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:11,320
I'm sorry.

542
00:41:22,670 --> 00:41:24,550
Before caring about my happiness,

543
00:41:26,380 --> 00:41:28,430
you should care about yours.

544
00:41:30,590 --> 00:41:32,430
Before seeing my wound,

545
00:41:32,930 --> 00:41:34,930
you should take care of yours first.

546
00:41:38,940 --> 00:41:40,850
You're a mess.

